column5: Headed out today for a ride to Couch with the mrs,s this morning. What a great day for a boat ride. Once we got into Couch,I had no satilite readings. So Im guessing I need a new chip for this area and the routes to GBay.  The ride back was awesome. 2+ waves coming from the south, and the boat was full out and it was a great ride. When we hit the mouth of Kempenfelt,it was glass. Oh BTW,LOTS of down rigging going on out there. Most I seen in years.
need more info  you should have sat reading with or without chip what gps unit do you have
no satellite readings means your unit might be toast  you should still get a reading regardless of what chip is in the unit
It came up as a wall on the screen. It,s not toast.It worked fine til there.  It,s a Garmin 178c sounder. The chip in it right now isLake ont to Montrel.
I knew you could. TY  Were off next week. Pick a day.
It,s not a big rush. Just when ever you can. TY again.
go buy a blank chip/card for you unit and maybe we can go bass fishing  friday in the morning and gps fixing  in the afternoon
if I understand the unit you have you need a microSD memory card  http://www.futureshop.ca/catalog/proddetai...6837&catid=
Get the "Tater Chip"!!!... it won't help you with where you're going...    ... but you'll be on such a "fat high", you won't care!!!

I have a Garmin 276c and the same card you have, it shows only the south end of GB Midland Penatang area, you need the next card over, you can go on Garmins website and get the card number, and also see the areas covered by each card.
I have the cd and one  license I have not used, so I think I can put the maps on a chip for him
